memtester (Utility for testing the memory subsystem)

A userspace utility for testing the memory subsystem for faults. It's portable
and should compile and work on any 32 or 64-bit Unix-like system. For hardware
developers, as of version 4.1.0, memtester can be told to test memory starting
at a particular physical address.

http://pyropus.ca/software/memtester/